point.

<span id="fn_754"></span>[276:2](sbe1926.htm#fr_754.md) This comparison of
Buddha's body to the golden mountain (sumeru) is a very frequent one,
and is probably allied in its origin with the idea of Bel, 'the great
mountain' (sadu rabu).

<span id="fn_755"></span>[276:3](sbe1926.htm#fr_755.md) The sense is, 'if
